            <handDesc hands="3">
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr">
                <desc>This manuscript is written in a good, regular hand of the <date>ixth cent.</date></desc>
              </handNote>
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr-Syrj">
                <desc>Greek vowels have been occasionally added, in most instances, it would seem, by later hands.</desc>
              </handNote>
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <desc>The <ref>hymns on foll. 1 a</ref>, <ref>178 b and 179</ref>, seem to be also in the hand of <persName>the scribe, the monk Simeon</persName>, though written currente calamo; and so also is the <ref>Index of the contents of the volume</ref>, fol. 1 b.</desc>
              </handNote>
